title_full:
MSYLMA

              —
              Dhil-un Taht Shajarat Al-Zaqum
            
              (Halcyon Veil)
label: Halcyon Veil
description:
One of 2019’s standout albums is now available on vinyl for the first time; the solo debut by Mecca-based Msylma is a compelling coming-of-age tale sung in classical Arabic and set to stark, mystic electronic production by Zuli, 1127 and the artist himself for Rabit’s often pioneering Halcyon Veil label.

description:
Jaw-dropping 2nd album by Logos, follow-up to his UK classic ‘Cold Mission’, full of clinical sci-fi sound design and stylized noir narrative riddled with club zingers, checking the electric blue pulse of UK Hardcore Musicks.

description:
Milan and Haunter Records’ Heith pushes into the abstract with mulchy brownian motion on the first dispatch from Saucers, a new label minted specifically for his gear.
